description.value: Blue glazed composition shabti of Pinudjem I decorated with black ink; column of hieroglyphic text down the front. The mummiform figure wears a wig with a uraeus, false beard, and a broad collar. The crossed arms hold two hoes. The face is small, the eyes painted large in black ink, the nose only vaguely modelled, and no mouth is indicated. The ink was applied in fairly loose brushstrokes.
